      // === Portfolio comment. ============
      section.comment(style="display:none")
        h3 THEORETICAL MOTIVATIONS
        p A progression of feedback, from audio to video.
        p What began as visual exploration of the surrounding space and feedback, ultimately turned into a performance piece. Soft, rhythmic colors appear on the screen based on the motions of the performer, capturing the visual environment and layering it back onto itself.
        h3 TECHNICAL DISCUSSION
        p The first instance of 'diaspora' was as a self-contained image generator, to be accompanied by audio from the performer. This slowly changed until the project became a sort of 'Video Jockey' device to complement recordings.
        p As the original motivation was to include the environment -- both audible and visible -- sound playback capabilities were added again. The latest version of the piece takes a set of pre-recorded samples, and alters them based on the brightness and motion in the piece.
        h3 DOCUMENTATION
        p A performance from March 2005 at Rx Gallery in San Francisco. This is a montage of a video performance that was choreographed live to pre-recorded music.
